Get Play-By-Play Data for NCAA Baseball Games

Source: R/ncaa_baseball_pbp.R
ncaa_baseball_pbp.Rd

Get Play-By-Play Data for NCAA Baseball Games

Usage

ncaa_baseball_pbp(game_info_url)

Arguments

game_info_url

The url for the game's play-by-play data. This can be found using the get_ncaa_schedule_info function.

Value

A data frame with play-by-play data for an individual game. |col_name |types | |:--------------|:---------| |date |character | |location |character | |attendance |logical | |inning |character | |inning_top_bot |character | |score |character | |batting |character | |fielding |character | |description |character |

Examples

# \donttest{
  x <- ncaa_schedule_info(736, 2021)$game_info_url[2]
  ncaa_baseball_pbp(game_info_url = x)
